               <birth when="0451">He was born at a place called Kurtam near Baṭnān (Batnae) in <date> 451</date>.</birth>
               
               <floruit notBefore="0473" notAfter="0521">He became a monk at the age of 22  in <date> 473</date>.
                  In his final years, he became a bishop of his native Baṭnān in <date> 519</date>.
                  He is best known for his extensive poetic output. It is believed that he composed 760 metrical homilies of which perhaps 250 have survived. 
                  He also composed hymns and numerous letters. His several compositions are also extant in Ethiopic. 
                  These works were translated from Arabic into Gǝʿǝz during the reign of King <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>
                  to be read on newly established feasts  for various saints.
               </floruit>
